guys I believe you better leave JJs music alone, you can be good to hear but its the presence of JJ as a person behind made the ultimate difference, like it wasn't all in his words he sang.. his songs are like a gush of stream that poured out of spring from some of the most delightful spring in the heaven.. It was more the soul than mere presence of the artist and for many of us he still stands taller than tall  amongst you.. leave his music untouched and pure...
